
[1]elysium

   ELYS'IUM, n. elyzh'um. [L. elysium.] In ancient mythology, a place
   assigned to happy souls after death; a place in the lower regions,
   furnished with rich fields, groves, shades, streams, &c., the seat of
   future happiness. Hence, any delightful place.
